      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/2/33",
      "text": [
        " اَلرَّجُلِ يَمُوتُ وَ عَلَيْهِ دَيْنٌ فَيَضْمَنُهُ ضَامِنٌ لِلْغُرَمَاءِ قَالَ \"إِذَا رَضِيَ بِهِ اَلْغُرَمَاءُ فَقَدْ بَرِئَتْ ذِمَّةُ اَلْمَيِّتِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3711 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Al-Hasan ibn Salih Al-Thawri, from Abu Abdillah (as), regarding a man who dies while owing a debt, and a guarantor guarantees it for the creditors.\nImam (as) said: \"If the creditors are satisfied with him, then the deceased is absolved of liability.\""
        ]
      }
    },
